By: Senators James of the 28th, Rahman of the 5th, Kemp of the 38th, Esteves of the 35th,
Harbison of the 15th and others
A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life and memory of Frankie Mae Arnold; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia mourns the loss of one of its most distinguished citizens
3 with the passing of Frankie Mae Arnold; and
4 WHEREAS, a resident of Fairburn, Georgia, for more than 70 years, she served as the first
5 African American elected to the Fairburn City Council, a position she held for 12 years; and
6 WHEREAS, she earned numerous honors and accolades in recognition of her dedicated
7 service, including being named Citizen of the Quarter by The Fairburn News in 1993, an
8 Outstanding Community Service Award, and a Leadership Award for the Old Atlanta Task
9 Force, a senior citizens volunteer group; and
10 WHEREAS, she gave inspiration to many through her high ideals, morals, and deep concern
11 for her fellow citizens, and the devotion, patience, and understanding she demonstrated to
12 her family and friends were admired by others; and
