13 WHEREAS, she was a person of magnanimous strengths with an unimpeachable reputation
14 for integrity, intelligence, fairness, and kindness, and by the example she made of her life,
15 she made this world a better place in which to live; and
16 WHEREAS, a compassionate and generous woman, Frankie Mae Arnold will long be
17 remembered for her love of family, friendship, and community and will be missed by all who
18 had the great fortune of knowing her.
19 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
20 join in honoring the life and memory of Frankie Mae Arnold and express their deepest and
21 most sincere regret at her passing.
22 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
23 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the family of
24 Frankie Mae Arnold.
